---
alwaysApply: true
---
rules:
  - id: architecture.module_dependency_structure
    description: |
      Module dependencies must be explicit, acyclic, and declared within designated interface boundaries.
      - Modules may only depend on public interfaces of other modules; internal details must remain encapsulated.
      - Circular dependencies (direct or indirect) are strictly prohibited; dependency injection or interface segregation must be used to break cycles.
      - Shared abstractions and foundational libraries must reside at the lowest architectural layer.
      - Dependency graphs must be documented and validated on major changes.
    severity: error

  - id: architecture.cognitive_pipeline_patterns
    description: |
      Only approved pipeline patterns may be used for cognitive processing.
      - All cognitive pipelines must follow the architectural blueprints (e.g., DAG, chain-of-responsibility, event-driven, with centralized orchestration where required).
      - Custom or ad hoc pipeline structures are prohibited unless reviewed and accepted in writing by architecture governance.
      - Input and output contracts (schemas, types, expected side effects) for each stage must be explicitly documented.
      - Pipeline extensibility and safe interception points should be provided for future enhancement.
    severity: error

  - id: architecture.routing_rules
    description: |
      Routing of data and execution must conform to standardized rules.
      - All cross-module and inter-pipeline calls must be routed through defined gateways or dispatchers.
      - No direct calls allowed between implementation details of different modules; use designated interfaces or message buses.
      - Routing logic must be isolated; business logic and routing are not to be intermixed.
      - Routing decisions must be deterministic and logged for traceability.
      - Unauthorized or undocumented dynamic routing, reflection-based invocation, or monkey-patching are prohibited.
    severity: error

  - id: architecture.evaluation_methods
    description: |
      All architectural mechanisms must include evaluation methods to verify correctness, performance, and compliance.
      - Each module and pipeline must define standardized evaluation hooks (unit, integration, contract, and scenario tests).
      - Evaluation criteria must be specified in architectural documentation and reviewed on each significant change.
      - Automated validation (linting, static analysis, contract checks) must run as part of CI/CD.
      - All deviations or flakiness must trigger root-cause analysis and remediation.
    severity: error

  - id: architecture.versioning_and_change_control
    description: |
      Architectural versioning and change control must follow strict discipline.
      - All public architectural interfaces and cognitive pipeline contracts must employ semantic versioning.
      - Breaking changes are only allowed with major version increments and require explicit migration guides.
      - All changes must be logged in architectural changelogs and communicated to all stakeholders.
      - Deprecated modules or interfaces must specify end-of-life timelines and backward-compatibility strategies.
      - No ad hoc or undocumented architecture changes are permitted.
    severity: error

  - id: architecture.rfc_requirement
    description: |
      All changes to core architecture require an approved RFC (Request for Comments) before implementation.
      - Core architecture files include: base_module.py, registry.py, orchestrator.py, server.py, client.py, and architecture rules
      - An RFC must be filed in `.cursor/rules/governance/RFC/` before making changes to core architecture
      - RFC must follow the standardized template format and include all required sections
      - RFC must be in APPROVED status before changes are allowed
      - RFC must be properly indexed in RFC_INDEX.md
      - Changes to core architecture without an approved RFC are strictly prohibited
      - See `.cursor/rules/governance/rfc_enforcement.mdc` for detailed RFC requirements
    severity: error

references:
  - https://martinfowler.com/articles/enterpriseArchitecture.html
  - https://cognitivesciencesociety.org/architectures-for-cognitive-models/
  - https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html
  - (Internal) Mavaia Design Blueprints, Section 4 ("Cognitive Pipeline Patterns")
  - (Internal) Mavaia Engineering Handbook, v2024.2, "Inter-module Dependency & Routing"
  - RFC Enforcement: .cursor/rules/governance/rfc_enforcement.mdc
  - RFC Template: .cursor/rules/governance/RFC/RFC_TEMPLATE.md
  - RFC Documentation: .cursor/rules/governance/RFC/README.md

